snippet.title: The why of the fly
snippet.description: ... ... I'm an addicted multi-tasker. I'm writing this journal, doing Suduko, chatting, listening to music and trying to catch that fly. ... ... Voices are strong today. I turned on the voice eliminator..music. They say that music calms the savage beast. Who are THEY any way? It does help quell my voices. WDAVE radio wasn't playing when I woke up today. ... ... I'm torn. I want to go back to the speakers group, but I don't wanna be called a circus. I more than likely won't go back. The anxiety I felt back then is still with me. Writing about it just now gave me a squirt of anxiety. ... ... I feel good. No depression, or anxiety..the bit of anxiety I had earlier is gone. ... ... Did someone say dessert? Maybe it was a voice in my head. Good idea though. We bought a dessert magazine with 135 recipes.... ...

snippet.title: Does omeprazole protect me from the side effects of Motrin?
snippet.description: ... I take 6 Motrin daily for pain control and I take omeprazole for GERD. My arthritis specialist said that as long as I am taking omeprazole I don't have to worry about the side effects of Motrin, but I thought omeprazole would protect only my stomach and not my duodenum. Will the omeprazole protect the duodenum also? ...

snippet.title: Is Free PSA of 12.1 a sign of cancer spreading ?
snippet.description: ... My father aged 84 years , under went scrotum removal operations in 2004 , when his PSA was at >100 and after surgery it came to 0.05 after one year , again in 2007 end it started rising and now we tested his Total PSA last week ie june 1st 2009 it was at 14.1 and his FREE PSA iS AT 12.1 . What does this shows ? Is his prostate cancer spreading slowly or what please reply to my query . ...
